00132 /* The OS/2 version of Netscape uses RC_DATA to define the
00133    mime types, file extensions, etc that are required.
00134    Use a vertical bar to separate types, end types with \0.
00135    FileVersion and ProductVersion are 32bit ints, all other
00136    entries are strings that MUST be terminated with a \0.
00137 
00138 AN EXAMPLE:
00139 
00140 RCDATA NP_INFO_ProductVersion { 1,0,0,1,}
00141 
00142 RCDATA NP_INFO_MIMEType    { "video/x-video|",
00143                              "video/x-flick\0" }
00144 RCDATA NP_INFO_FileExtents { "avi|",
00145                              "flc\0" }
00146 RCDATA NP_INFO_FileOpenName{ "MMOS2 video player(*.avi)|",
00147                              "MMOS2 Flc/Fli player(*.flc)\0" }
00148 
00149 RCDATA NP_INFO_FileVersion       { 1,0,0,1 }
00150 RCDATA NP_INFO_CompanyName       { "Netscape Communications\0" }
00151 RCDATA NP_INFO_FileDescription   { "NPAVI32 Extension DLL\0"
00152 RCDATA NP_INFO_InternalName      { "NPAVI32\0" )
00153 RCDATA NP_INFO_LegalCopyright    { "Copyright Netscape Communications \251 1996\0"
00154 RCDATA NP_INFO_OriginalFilename  { "NVAPI32.DLL" }
00155 RCDATA NP_INFO_ProductName       { "NPAVI32 Dynamic Link Library\0" }
00156 */
00157 /* RC_DATA types for version info - required */
00158 #define NP_INFO_ProductVersion      1
00159 #define NP_INFO_MIMEType            2
00160 #define NP_INFO_FileOpenName        3
00161 #define NP_INFO_FileExtents         4
00162 /* RC_DATA types for version info - used if found */
00163 #define NP_INFO_FileDescription     5
00164 #define NP_INFO_ProductName         6
00165 /* RC_DATA types for version info - optional */
00166 #define NP_INFO_CompanyName         7
00167 #define NP_INFO_FileVersion         8
00168 #define NP_INFO_InternalName        9
00169 #define NP_INFO_LegalCopyright      10
00170 #define NP_INFO_OriginalFilename    11

00308 /*
00309  *   The following masks are applied on certain platforms to NPNV and
00310  *   NPPV selectors that pass around pointers to COM interfaces. Newer
00311  *   compilers on some platforms may generate vtables that are not
00312  *   compatible with older compilers. To prevent older plugins from
00313  *   not understanding a new browser's ABI, these masks change the
00314  *   values of those selectors on those platforms. To remain backwards
00315  *   compatible with different versions of the browser, plugins can
00316  *   use these masks to dynamically determine and use the correct C++
00317  *   ABI that the browser is expecting. This does not apply to Windows
00318  *   as Microsoft's COM ABI will likely not change.
00319  */
00320 
00321 #define NP_ABI_GCC3_MASK  0x10000000
00322 /*
00323  *   gcc 3.x generated vtables on UNIX and OSX are incompatible with
00324  *   previous compilers.
00325  */
00326 #if (defined(XP_UNIX) && defined(__GNUC__) && (__GNUC__ >= 3))
00327 #define _NP_ABI_MIXIN_FOR_GCC3 NP_ABI_GCC3_MASK
00328 #else
00329 #define _NP_ABI_MIXIN_FOR_GCC3 0
00330 #endif
00331 
00332 #if defined(XP_MACOSX)
00333 #define NP_ABI_MACHO_MASK 0x01000000
00334 #define _NP_ABI_MIXIN_FOR_MACHO NP_ABI_MACHO_MASK
00335 #else
00336 #define _NP_ABI_MIXIN_FOR_MACHO 0
00337 #endif
00338 
00339 #define NP_ABI_MASK (_NP_ABI_MIXIN_FOR_GCC3 | _NP_ABI_MIXIN_FOR_MACHO)
